  dialogue:
  - What's the problem?
  - 'In fact, why is our food thrown out? '
  - It went bad.
  - What?
  - Even the ones packaged in cans started rotting.
  - That shouldn't be possible.
  - Did you get some with faulty packaging?
  - It doesn't matter now. I went fishing earlier to make up for the loss...
  - ...but there was nothing out there.
  - You'll be going out tonight to try again.
  - Why can't you do it? You already went out before.
  - I lost my sea-legs, lad. I can only handle so much of the ocean waves now.
  - Are you sure you can handle the lighthouse by yourself?
  - Are you questioning me, lad?
  - I said you're going fishing so you go out there and fish.
  - Got that?
  - Yes, sir.
